reference:
Predefined variables





  PHP provides a large number of predefined variables to any script. The
  variables represent everything from
  external variables to
  built-in environment variables, last error messages to last retrieved
  headers.




  Superglobals


   Superglobals are built-in variables that are always available in all scopes.
   These variables are:

    $GLOBALS
    $_SERVER
    $_GET
    $_POST
    $_FILES
    $_COOKIE
    $_SESSION
    $_REQUEST
    $_ENV




    Superglobals cannot be used as 
    variable variables
    inside functions or class methods.






